Kenyan leasing company, Vehicle and Equipment Leasing Ltd (VAELL) has entered the Ugandan market by taking up Airtel Uganda as a client. The top leasing firm will now be leasing 43 Ford Ranger units to the Ugandan telco for a period of 48 months. Anna Asio, the VAELL Leasing Manager said VAELL has invested over Sh400 million in the Uganda market this year. She added that the investment demonstrates VAELL&rsquo;s confidence in the telecommunications sector in East Africa, which will be driving economies in the next decade. VAELL also has a car leasing agreement with the Kenyan government.